# Task: Nested Logic Test (Depth 3)
# Interface:
Class: Solution
Method: checkNested(self, x0: int, x1: int, x2: int) -> bool

# Objective:
This is a test of structural nesting. Return True ONLY if all the following conditions are met:
1. x0 is greater than 0
2. x1 is greater than 0
3. x2 is greater than 0

Each condition must be checked inside the previous one (nested if statements).
lisp_spec:
(task
  (name "checkNested")
  (signature ((x0 int) (x1 int) (x2 int)) bool)
  (constraints
    (constraint "All input parameters must be integers.")
    (constraint "The function should return a boolean value.")
  )
  (goal
    (description "Check if all three input parameters are greater than 0, with each condition checked inside the previous one using nested if statements.")
    (rule "If x0 is not greater than 0, return False")
    (rule "If x1 is not greater than 0 and x0 was greater than 0, return False")
    (rule "If x2 is not greater than 0 and both previous conditions were met, return False")
    (return "Return True if all three input parameters are greater than 0.")
  )
)
